63.7	Peter_I_of_Russia	Peter the Great	Peter the Great, Peter I or Pyotr Alexeyevich Romanov (Russian: ) (9 June 1672 â€“ 8 February 1725)note 1 ruled the Tsardom of Russia and later the Russian Empire from 7 May 1682 until his death, jointly ruling before 1696 with his half-brother. In numerous successful wars he expanded the Tsardom into a huge empire that became a major European power. According to historian James Cracraft, he led a cultural revolution that replaced the traditionalist and medieval social and political system with a modern, scientific, Europe-oriented, and rationalist system.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/Peter_the_Great_Signature.svg/125px-Peter_the_Great_Signature.svg.png
